The paper deals with the verification of multi-agent systems using symmetry transformations, which is a topic that falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper specifically focuses on multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and uses reachability analysis techniques (cs.RO) and virtual systems (cs.AI) to achieve its goals. Finally, the paper also discusses experimental results (cs.LG) to demonstrate the effectiveness of the proposed approach.
